      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That sudden \"popping\" sensation followed by deafness is likely a ruptured eardrum (perforation) caused by a loud noise, rather than simple tinnitus or wax blockage. A perforated eardrum often causes significant hearing loss, ringing, and sometimes otorrhea (drainage), which requires immediate medical attention to prevent further damage. Since I am an AI, I cannot provide a physical exam or admit you to a hospital, so your best option is to drive yourself to the closest emergency room in Oslo immediately to rule out serious injury. Please do not delay seeking care, as sudden sensorineural hearing loss also needs urgent treatment within the first 24-48 hours.",
